<div class="quotetitle">Tenzen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Why does the Second hand take up more resources than the Second counter?<br /></div><br />The &quot;digital&quot; is just two digits of text, whereas the &quot;second-hand&quot; is graphical and has to be redrawn every second.<br /><br />Check your task manager or a similar app that shows your cpu cycles. Turn the second-hand off, check the cpu or graphics usage, and then turn the second-hand on. Then watch the cpu-usage go up! (depending on how powerful your graphics processor or CPU is)<br /><br />On an old low-powered PC I had, I noticed the second-hand was consuming more than 5% of my cpu! So I turned it off.<br /><br />Anyhow, the request about the seconds ticking in the task-bar is no big deal. I suppose I was just looking back with nostalgia at my old 32-bit XP system.... <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_wink.gif" alt=";-)" title="Wink" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=447">aqk</a> — Tue Mar 12, 2013 9:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
